100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 25, 1926, a significant political shift occurred as the British Parliament debated proposals for increased autonomy in India, reflecting growing nationalist sentiments. In the United States, the U.S. Supreme Court upheld the constitutionality of the National Prohibition Act, igniting further discussions on the impact of alcohol bans. Meanwhile, in Germany, Chancellor Wilhelm Marx faced mounting pressure as economic instability continued to challenge the Weimar Republic.
